teal.sim.simulation

Class Simulation3D

  • java.lang.Object
    • teal.core.AbstractElement
      • teal.sim.simulation.Simulation3D
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.beans.PropertyChangeListener, java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener, HasID, TElement, TElementManager, THasPropertyChange, HasFramework, HasEngineControl, TSimulation, HasGUI
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SimEM, SimKinematic, SimWorld

    public abstract class Simulation3D
extends AbstractElement
implements TSimulation
    The abstract class Simulation3D implements TSimulation and provides management for a simulation which includes a 3D viewer and simulation engine specified in a derived class. All elements related to a specific simulation are managed by the Sim these could include Actions, simulated objects and controls. As envisioned a simulation will support an XML loader/dumper interface and should be able to be basic unit assigned to a TFramework which supports Simulations. It may be extended into a simulation with a default constructor and specified Engine.
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.9 $
    Author:
    Phil Bailey
    See Also:
    SimWorld, SimEM, Serialized Form
